abstract:

A journey of predicting skills shortages with real-time data. The study integrates online job ads with traditional datasets, offering a nuanced understanding of skill demands. We will present the results of the model tuning and applications, and the results on Italian and UK data.
---
full_description:

Explore the predictive power of online job ads in anticipating skill shortages, a critical aspect for effective workforce planning. Leveraging machine learning and multi-dimensional datasets, this study combines national statistical sources with job postings data to enhance the accuracy and granularity of predictions. Delve into the methodology, from quantifying skill importance to forecasting shortages and discover actionable insights to guide policies and strategies for a more aligned and efficient labor market.
